author: hrmx#0
content:
# Revised ESSS Website
Hello @everyone!
As the new year begins and new students arrive (welcome <@&1018237826082553936>s), I had a goal to revise the website to offer a more modern and practical page, while staying as cosistent to what students are used to from the year before. Some new features that are included are:
- Meeting and Event Dates and Times are now accessible home screen
- Announcements are easy to access from the website (if you are seeing this from the website, welcome! :D)
- A slicker webpage while keeping everything important
- And more ideas to be released!

As this is still in development (and you may catch some obvious bugs along the way which are being fixed at the moment), we are looking for suggestions on how to make this better for you guys. Feel free to offer suggestions either in our suggestions channel, DMing me, or the email mentioned on the website.

Best of luck to everyone semester!
https://www.sfu.ca/esss

author: hannahkitty04#1693
content:
Hello everyone. I wanted to share this reminder about the event that WIE is holding tonight!✨✨

Are you looking to improve your resume or explore co-op opportunities in the vehicle software industry? In collaboration with Tesla, WiE SFU is hosting a resume building workshop and work opportunities info session today! 

Join Tesla recruiters for advice on resume building tips and learn more about internship & full-time opportunities in Vehicle Firmware & Embedded Systems! 
📣DATE: Wednesday, July 19th, 2023 
🕙TIME: 6:15pm - 7:15pm PST
📍LOCATION: Microsoft Teams

Just a note on using Microsoft Teams, you may need to log in to your SFU Office 365 account before joining the call. Also, if you do not have Microsoft Teams installed on your device, you can always join from a browser.
 
If you have any questions or if you have any trouble joining the Teams meeting today, please don't hesitate to reach out to me or any of the WiE SFU team members via email or Discord and we will do our best to make sure everyone is able to join in. 

*participants should already have the link. Any questions can be directed to <@885299758103674900> (WIE’s VP Extternal)
